EDA Summary (Text Format):

EDA was performed to understand employee behavior, relationships between variables, and attrition patterns. Key steps:

Basic data inspection

Handling missing values

Visualizing attrition distribution

Comparing attrition across departments

Salary vs attrition comparison

Overtime impact on attrition

Work-life balance vs attrition

Job satisfaction distribution

Correlation heatmap to identify strong relationships

Key Findings:

Employees doing overtime showed higher attrition.

Lower monthly income groups had higher attrition.

Job roles like Sales and IT had higher turnover.

Longer commute distance increased attrition probability.

Low job satisfaction strongly correlated with leaving.

BI Dashboard Content (Text Explanation):

The Power BI dashboard includes:

Attrition by department

Attrition by job role

Attrition by salary band

Attrition by education

Attrition by gender

Attrition by distance from home

Attrition by job satisfaction

Filters for department, salary, overtime

KPI cards: Total employees, total attrition, attrition %

This dashboard helps HR visualize the risk areas instantly.

Machine Learning Model Explanation:

A predictive model was built to identify employees likely to leave.

Steps:

Categorical encoding (gender, department, job role, etc.)

Feature scaling where required.

Train-test split.

Model training using:

Logistic Regression

Random Forest Classifier

Evaluation using accuracy and classification report.

Feature importance extraction to show key attrition drivers.

Important Predictive Features:

Overtime

Monthly income

Job satisfaction

Years at company

Distance from home

Work-life balance

Real-Time Use Cases for HR:

Real-time attrition alerts for high-risk employees

Monitoring departments with rising turnover

Improving employee satisfaction programs

Adjusting compensation for underpaid job roles

Workforce planning and resource allocation

Reducing burnout by monitoring overtime hours

Identifying training needs

